U.K. Foreign Secretary Fears New Arab Democracies May Fail, Times Reports

-- B y   J o h n   S i m p s o n
-- 
2011-07-28T01:36:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-28/u-k-foreign-secretary-fears-new-arab-democracies-may-fail-times-reports.html
U.K. Foreign Secretary  William Hague 
worries that the democratic gains of popular revolutions in the
 Middle East  are threatened by deep-rooted problems that the
fledgling governments may be too weak to deal with, the London-
based Times reported, citing an interview.  Hague expressed particular concern over  Egypt , and urged
European leaders to help prevent the power struggle in Cairo
from allowing the pivotal country to slide backward, the
newspaper said.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
